[{"id":42705,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b6aad69a-44c2-4b95-a130-e4c63c0e6dab-9896638.PNG\" style=\"width: 251px; height: 200px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6443dbaa-636d-4a50-9c95-01ae1fa836a4-9896638_1.PNG\" style=\"width: 254px; height: 200px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b2a6bc8a-ee46-4627-9298-b29624c4c849-9896638_2.PNG\" style=\"width: 260px; height: 200px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8b3a6642-d65a-41b5-98d7-f6ac5a9870bd-9896638_3.PNG\" style=\"width: 257px; height: 200px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>A simple pendulum consists of a point mass attached to an inextensible string and suspended from a support.</p><p>The formula to calculate the time period&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>T</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;of a simple pendulum is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>where,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math>&nbsp;is the length of the pendulum and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math>&nbsp;is the acceleration due to gravity.</p><p>Simplify equation (1) to obtain the relation between the time period and the length.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnspacing=\"0px\" columnalign=\"right center left\"><mtr><mtd><msup><mi>T</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msup></mtd><mtd><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">4</mn><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#215;</mo><mi>&#120001;</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8733;</mo></mtd><mtd><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Equation (2) suggests that the graph between the square of the time period versus the length of the pendulum is a straight line passing through the origin.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (01 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42698,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The formula to calculate the potential energy of the particle executing SHM is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>The formula to calculate the kinetic energy of the same particle is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Divide equation (1) by equation (2) to obtain the required ratio.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mi>P</mi><mi>K</mi></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Substitute&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;into equation (3) to calculate the required ratio.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mi>P</mi><mi>K</mi></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msup><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mstyle><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42797,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/633e0c9b-94ac-48f9-8260-4500bfb8ee85-image.png\" style=\"width: 188px; height: 181px;\" /><br /><br />Angle covered to meet <math><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mn>60</mn></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></math><br /><br />Therefore,&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac> <mi>&#952;</mi> <mi>&#969;</mi> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo><mfrac> <mi>&#960;</mi> <mn>3</mn> </mfrac> <mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac> <mi>T</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo><mfrac> <mi>T</mi> <mn>6</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> </math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":42665,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$\\pi \\sqrt{\\frac{2 M}{\\rho A g}}$","$\\pi \\sqrt{\\frac{\\rho A}{M g}}$","$2 \\pi \\sqrt{\\frac{\\rho A}{M g}}$","$2 \\pi \\sqrt{\\frac{M}{\\rho A g}}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"When the block is depressed by distance $x$, the additional buoyant force is $F = \\rho Agx$ acting upward as restoring force. <br>Equation of motion: $M\\frac{d^2x}{dt^2} = -\\rho Agx$. <br>This gives $\\omega^2 = \\frac{\\rho Ag}{M}$. <br>Period of oscillation: $T = \\frac{2\\pi}{\\omega} = 2\\pi\\sqrt{\\frac{M}{\\rho Ag}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (24 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42801,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/21b66e55-5186-417b-9613-518d5b4b7d97-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 181px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/15da6808-9b0d-4c2c-9f91-98dc8a77ff25-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 176px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/15acf882-f871-4cd9-94a0-215083bb3567-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 188px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ba085bc6-1f8a-47b2-829e-efb56998db87-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 180px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<math><mo>&#8757;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></math><br /><br />Also, <math><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mrow></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mi>&#160;</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">cos</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mi>&#160;</mi></mrow></mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><msup><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />As, <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>A</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">cos</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>A</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><msup><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>x</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><msqrt><msup><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></msqrt><mi>&#160;</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mo>&#177;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>A</mi></math><br /><br />Which is possible only in option (C)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (10 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":42671,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$\\theta_1 l_2^2=\\theta_2 l_1^2$","$\\theta_1 l_1=\\theta_2 l_2$","$\\theta_1 l_1^2=\\theta_2 l_2^2$","$\\theta_1 l_2=\\theta_2 l_1$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\omega=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\mathrm{g}}{\\ell}} \\\\ & \\alpha=-\\omega^2 \\theta \\\\ & \\therefore \\frac{\\mathrm{~g}}{\\ell_1} \\theta_1=\\frac{\\mathrm{g}}{\\ell_2} \\theta_2 \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\theta_1 \\ell_2=\\theta_2 \\ell_2\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (4 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42820,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$\\frac{\\pi}{3}$","$\\frac{\\pi}{4}$","$\\frac{\\pi}{6}$","$\\frac{\\pi}{2}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\phi_1=0$\n$\\phi_2=\\frac{\\pi}{2}$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/PzldBGdqHewVP25tXgzdEF4qL4lhjY-uz7LZtuIZlXY.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2011","image":null},{"id":42800,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>52</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>26</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>39</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>65</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"Case-I<br /><br />In equilibrium<br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">up</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">mg</mi></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></msub><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mi>A</mi><mi>h</mi><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></msub><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>L</mi><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub><mi>g</mi><mo>…</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>…</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bnuuu.JPG\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 278px;\" /><br /><br />Case-II<br /><br />Let block is pressed by x more in liquid<br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msubsup><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msubsup><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">mg</mi></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">net</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A </mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></mrow></mfenced><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">AL</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">net</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ah</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ax</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">AL</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>. . . . . . . . . . (2)<br /><br />from equation (1) &amp; (2)<br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">net</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ax</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g&nbsp;</mi></math>restoring force in upward direction<br /><br /><math><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>A</mi><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></msub><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">α</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x for SHM</mi></math><br /><br />and <math><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />so <math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />so <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>650</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>54</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>900</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>39</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">cm</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (11 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":42778,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$K_{2}=2 K_{1}$","$\\mathrm{K}_{2}=\\frac{\\mathrm{K}_{1}}{2}$","$\\mathrm{K}_{2}=\\frac{\\mathrm{K}_{1}}{4}$","$K_{2}=K$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$K=\\frac{1}{2} m \\omega^{2} x^{2}$\r\n\r\n$\\Rightarrow K_{\\max }=\\frac{1}{2} m \\omega^{2} A^{2}$\r\n\r\nA $=L \\theta$\r\n\r\n$\\omega=\\sqrt{\\frac{g}{L}}$\r\n\r\n$\\Rightarrow K=\\frac{1}{2} m \\cdot \\frac{g}{L} \\cdot L^{2} \\theta^{2}$\r\n\r\n$=\\frac{1}{2} m g L \\theta^{2}$\r\n\r\n$\\therefore \\frac{K_{1}}{K_{2}}=\\frac{L}{2 L}=\\frac{1}{2} \\Rightarrow K_{2}=2 K_{1}$\r\n\r\n$\\therefore \\frac{\\mathrm{K}_{1}}{\\mathrm{~K}_{2}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{L}}{2 \\mathrm{~L}}=\\frac{1}{2} \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{K}_{2}=2 \\mathrm{~K}_{1}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42724,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The time period of spring block system is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>.</p><p>In both the cases springs are connected in parallel,</p><p>In case <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>k</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;and total mass is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi></math>. Therefore,</p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfenced><msub><mi>k</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>In case&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>k</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;and total mass is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>. Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mfenced><mi>m</mi></mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42707,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>37</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>18</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The maximum potential energy of a block executing simple harmonic motion is&nbsp;given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p>As, kinetic energy of particle executing SHM is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>.<p>So, kinetic energy of block&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>at</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msubsup><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42817,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cNCG8QEtftl450puhVNEe-8KOR8wNc0Gtvt50hQ7XCI.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ymZ24fJjM3-djnjRFGnxljXA0dAO4BAddDrSwC8AuEk.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/31Y86z8yvD9mKsbgSFvjo9EnGxQRjve9fvgQy2wNJqc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/QFHwrQ1KK-fM7FoOXwzsz9ldbfiUe03DnLChTg4Ojh8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Displacement $y(t)=A \\sin (\\mathrm{w} t+\\phi)$ [Given]\nFor $\\phi=\\frac{2 \\pi}{3}$\nat $t=0 ; y=A \\sin \\phi=A \\sin \\frac{2 \\pi}{3}$\n$$\n=A \\sin 120^{\\circ}=0.87 \\mathrm{~A}\\left[\\because \\sin 120^{\\circ} \\simeq 0.866\\right]\n$$\nGraph (a) depicts $y=0.87 A$ at $t=0$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":42723,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>When two&nbsp;waves&nbsp;of the&nbsp;same frequency superimpose, the resultant amplitude is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mrow><mi>resultant</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msubsup><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#981;</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#981;</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#981;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#981;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>&#981;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>Phase difference <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn></math>&nbsp;degree</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42666,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$\\frac{4}{3} E$","4E","3E","$2 E$"],"answer":2,"solution":"For blocks hanging in equilibrium, spring extensions are:<br>$x_A = \\frac{m_A g}{k_A} = \\frac{100g}{k_A}$ and $x_B = \\frac{m_B g}{k_B} = \\frac{200g}{k_B}$.<br>Energy stored:<br>$E = \\frac{1}{2}k_A x_A^2 = \\frac{5000g^2}{k_A}$ and $U_B = \\frac{1}{2}k_B x_B^2 = \\frac{20000g^2}{k_B}$.<br>Taking ratio: $\\frac{U_B}{E} = 4 \\cdot \\frac{k_A}{k_B}$.<br>Given $4k_A = 3k_B$, we have $\\frac{k_A}{k_B} = \\frac{3}{4}$.<br>Therefore: $U_B = 4E \\cdot \\frac{3}{4} = 3E$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42805,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["$a+b x-c x^2$","$\\mathrm{bx}^2$","$a-b x+c x^2$","$-b x$"],"answer":3,"solution":"In linear S.H.M., the restoring force acting on particle should always be proportional to the displacement of the particle and directed towards the equilibrium position. i.e., $\\mathrm{F} \\propto \\mathrm{x}$\nor $\\mathrm{F}=-\\mathrm{bx}$ where $\\mathrm{b}$ is a positive constant.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (12 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":42731,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Oscillations","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>3</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Maximum velocity is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mi>A</mi></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/410f6e8b-ab56-475f-bdcf-0e037fc21bb4-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 179px;\" /></p><p>Here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></msqrt><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></msqrt><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>50</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>100</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p>Thus, ratio of amplitude is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 2)","image":null}]